{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Enforce release-source authorization + version lockstep before publication\n\nRe-anchor the release to the proven OSS pattern: initiate it from the protected\n`main` branch via `workflow_dispatch` (so the source is reviewed-and-landed **by\nconstruction**), assert version-lockstep before build (pydantic's pre-build version\ncheck), and gate production publication on a required-reviewers environment (uv's\nrelease-gate + PyPA Trusted Publishing). (Readiness Finding 1 — verified VALID\nagainst `release.yml:17-21`, `infra/terraform-github/main.tf:23-101`,\n`docs/releasing.md`.)\n\n## Why\n\n`main` is constrained to the Gerrit replication deploy key, but `refs/tags/v*` was\ndeliberately left open (`infra/terraform-github/main.tf:23-28`) so a human can push\na `v*` tag to drive PyPI + MCP-registry + GitHub-Release publication\n(`release.yml:17-21`, jobs `build`/`publish`/`github_release`/`mcp_registry`). The\nonly gate anywhere is `if: github.event_name == 'push' && startsWith(github.ref,\n'refs/tags/v')` (release.yml:53/81/116) — nothing checks that the tagged SHA is an\nancestor of (or equal to) reviewed `main`, verifies any Gerrit/CI result for that\nexact SHA, or asserts version consistency. A PEP 740\nattestation would correctly name this repo's workflow but cannot distinguish a tag\non reviewed `main` from a tag on any other commit. Separately, the three version\nvalues (`pyproject.toml:10`, `server.json` top-level and `packages[].version`) are\nkept in lockstep only by a manual runbook (`docs/releasing.md`), so a future\nmismatch would publish disagreeing versions across the PyPI / GitHub-Release / MCP\nchannels with no machine check.\n\n## What\n\nAdopt uv's proven release process and pydantic's pre-build version check, in this\norder of control strength:\n\n- **Primary control — initiate from `main` via `workflow_dispatch` (source reviewed\n  by construction).** Make `workflow_dispatch` the sanctioned release trigger, run\n  from the `main` ref. Because the GitHub mirror's `main` is exactly the\n  Gerrit-reviewed-and-landed history, releasing from `main` guarantees the source is\n  reviewed **by construction** — the same guarantee the wider OSS world gets from\n  \"release only from the protected branch.\" This replaces \"accept whatever commit an\n  arbitrary pushed tag points at,\" which was the actual divergence from consensus.\n- **Version-lockstep, before build (pydantic pattern).** A first job parses the\n  intended version and every manifest and asserts exact equality **before build**:\n  `version_input == project.version == server.json.version ==\n  each server.json.packages[].version`; mismatch fails before build.\n- **Human authorization — required-reviewers environment (uv release-gate + PyPA\n  Trusted Publishing).** `build` `needs:` the version-check job, and `publish`\n  depends on the `pypi` deployment environment with required reviewers, so production\n  publication needs a second human's approval. This + release-from-`main` are the\n  load-bearing controls, and they are exactly the mainstream OSS pattern.\n- **The workflow creates the `v*` tag after checks pass** (uv, and the finding's own\n  remediation: \"create the release tag only after the source and version checks pass,\n  rather than accepting an already-created human tag as the initial fact\"). The\n  GitHub-release and MCP jobs derive the version from the dispatch input / the tag the\n  workflow just created.\n- **Defense-in-depth — ancestry assertion.** Keep the existing `v*` tag-push trigger\n  as a fallback, but route it through the same checks, and additionally assert the\n  release SHA is reachable from `origin/main` via\n  `git merge-base --is-ancestor \"$GITHUB_SHA\" origin/main` (checkout with\n  `fetch-depth: 0` + `git fetch origin main`, since a shallow clone defeats ancestry —\n  the repo documents this at `reconcile-bridge.yml:83-88` and `verify-identity.yaml`\n  already uses `fetch-depth: 0`). With dispatch-from-`main` this is redundant belt-and-\n  suspenders; it exists so a stray tag push can never bypass the gate.\n- **Tag-push restriction stays OUT of scope (unchanged, deliberate).** `main.tf:23-28`\n  documents that the `tag_lock` resource was removed because GitHub offers **no viable\n  bypass actor** for tag writes in this mirror topology, and the contract test\n  `tests/unit/test_mirror_lock_terraform.py::test_module_is_main_only_no_tag_lock`\n  codifies \"no tag lock\". We do not restrict *who* can push a tag; the\n  release-from-`main` + environment-approval + ancestry controls make it unnecessary.\n- Record the approved SHA, tag, manifest versions, and artifact hashes in release\n  evidence (a job summary / uploaded evidence file).\n\n## Scope\n\n- `.github/workflows/release.yml` — add a `workflow_dispatch` trigger with a version\n  input (release from `main`); a `version-check` job (lockstep assertion, before\n  build); a tag-creation step after checks pass; `build`/`publish` gated on the check\n  job + the required-reviewers `pypi` environment; keep the `v*` tag trigger as a\n  gated fallback with the ancestry assertion.\n- `infra/terraform-github/main.tf` — **no change** (the deliberate no-tag-lock\n  decision and its contract test stand; see the out-of-scope rationale above).\n- `docs/releasing.md` — document the dispatch-from-`main` process, the version-lockstep\n  invariant, and the required environment reviewers. **Section ownership:** this story\n  owns the \"Release-source authorization\" section; Finding 3 owns the \"Build-once\"\n  section and Finding 4 owns the \"Pinning\" section, so the three concurrent release\n  stories do not overlap-edit the same headings.\n- Out of scope: the build-once / pinning work (Findings 3 and 4 — separate stories\n  that also touch `release.yml`; coordinate ordering per the epic).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] The release is initiated by `workflow_dispatch` running from the `main` ref (a\n  version input), so the released source is reviewed-and-landed `main` by construction\n  — verified by the workflow definition (a `workflow_dispatch` trigger with a version\n  input) and by `docs/releasing.md` describing dispatch-from-`main` as the sanctioned\n  path.\n- [ ] A `version-check` job asserts `version_input`, `pyproject.toml` version,\n  `server.json` version, and every `server.json.packages[].version` are equal and\n  fails before build on any mismatch — verified by a run where the values deliberately\n  disagree, which exits in the check job before build with a message naming each\n  mismatched source.\n- [ ] The workflow creates the `v*` tag only after the version-check passes; `build`,\n  `publish`, `github_release`, and `mcp_registry` do not start unless the check job\n  succeeds (they `needs:` it, directly or transitively).\n- [ ] The retained `v*` tag-push fallback additionally asserts the SHA is reachable\n  from `origin/main` (`git merge-base --is-ancestor`, checkout `fetch-depth: 0` +\n  `git fetch origin main`) — verified by a tag on a non-ancestor commit failing before\n  any build/publish job, and a tag on a non-tip ancestor passing (proving no shallow-\n  clone false-negative).\n- [ ] Publication safety does not depend on restricting tag-push identity: the story\n  documents that release-from-`main` + the required-reviewers `pypi` environment are\n  the load-bearing controls, and `infra/terraform-github/main.tf` is left unchanged\n  (the no-tag-lock contract test still passes).\n- [ ] `docs/releasing.md` documents the dispatch-from-`main` process, the\n  version-lockstep invariant, and the environment-reviewer requirement.\n- [ ] [operator-attested] The live `pypi` GitHub environment has required reviewers\n  enabled so production publication needs an independent approval (attested by a\n  comment naming the environment settings screenshot/URL or an org-admin confirmation).\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` pass, and the change lands via the\n  Gerrit two-vote gate."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784060281273284001,"uuid":"027fe7cc-2a1a-4e3c-a36b-8f05680211b7"}